</div>
<p>The reason for&nbsp;renaming&nbsp;some of the concepts in Exponential 5.x=
 was to use terms which might be more familiar to users coming from other C=
MS and avoid confusion with terms used in OOP programming.</p>
<h3 id=3D"IntroforExponential4.x/3.xdevelopers-Newconcepts:">New concepts:</h=
3>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-inf=
ormation">
<span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-info confluence-informa=
tion-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<p>You can also refer to <a href=3D"http://symfony.com/doc/current/glossary=
.html" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Symfony glossary page</a> a=
s many of the following concepts are the same or taken from Symfony.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><strong>5.x</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><strong>Description</strong></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><strong><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">Co=
ntroller</span></strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>An OOP version of what was called "<strong>mo=
dule</strong>" in 4.x, <strong>should extend</strong>&nbsp;<code>eZ\Bundle\=
EzPublishCoreBundle\Controller</code>.<br>A good start is to read <a href=
=3D"http://symfony.com/doc/current/book/controller.html" class=3D"external-=
link" rel=3D"nofollow">Symfony documentation on this topic</a>.&nbsp;</p></=
td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><strong><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">Ac=
tion</span></strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>The method on the Controller, similarly to wh=
at was referred to as "<strong>view</strong>" in 4.x, contains business log=
ic bootstrap (business logic should be done in services).</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><strong>View</strong></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">The <strong>template</strong> that=
 displays the result of the "action", can be either .twig (default) or .php=
.<br>Note that <strong>Twig is highly recommended</strong> as it has <span>=
Exponential specific </span>helpers.&nbsp;</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><strong>Service</strong></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">A Service is a generic term for an=
y PHP object that performs a specific task and thus contains business logic=
. Services are instantiated and maintained a the <em>service container</em>=
.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><strong>Service Container</strong>=
</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">A Service Container, also known as=
 a <em>Dependency Injection Container</em>, is a special object that manage=
s the instantiation of services inside an application. Instead of creating =
services directly, the developer trains the service container (via configur=
ation) on how to create the services.<br><a href=3D"http://symfony.com/doc/=
current/book/service_container.html" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollo=
w">See Symfony documentation on the service container</a>.&nbsp;</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><strong>Render</strong></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">A function that allows you to <em>=
Embed</em> other controller calls, as in <em>Hierarchically</em> render oth=
er controllers and embed it in your result. This effectively removes the ne=
ed for having business logic in template using <strong>fetch</strong> funct=
ions, session management and so on.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><strong><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">Bu=
ndle</span></strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">An "<stron=
g>extension</strong>" in Symfony Framework and hence the extensions of eZ P=
ublish 5.x kernel.</span></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><strong>Console</strong></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><code>exponential/console</code> is =
the starting point of all console commands in Symfony2 (referred to as <cod=
e>app/console</code> in Symfony2 documentation) and Exponential 5.x kernel, =
use <code>php exponential/console -h</code> from the root of your install usi=
ng command line to get started.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><strong><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">web/<=
/span></strong></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>The public folder of your site, two console c=
ommands exists to symlink/hard-copy <em>Bundles</em> and <em>Legacy</em> as=
sets respectively.<br>Front controllers (index.php/index_dev.php) can be mo=
dified to fit your needs.<em>&nbsp;</em></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><strong>exponential/</strong></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">The application folder (aka <code>=
app/</code> <a href=3D"http://symfony.com/doc/current/book/page_creation.ht=
ml#the-application-app-directory" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">=
in the Symfony documentation</a>). <br>It contains the main Kernel class wh=
ere you can declare the bundles you want to use. You will also find <code>c=
ache/</code>, <code>logs/</code> and main <code>config/</code> folders. It =
can also contain application-level resource files, such as global templates=
 (<code>exponential/Resources/</code>).</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><strong>src/</strong></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">This is where your <a href=3D"http=
://symfony.com/doc/current/book/page_creation.html#the-source-src-directory=
" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">application code</a> stands (fro=
m your own bundles)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><strong>vendor/</strong></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">In this directory stand all your d=
ependencies (3rd party bundles/libs, Exponential codebase, Symfony codebase.=
..)</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h1 class=3D"western" id=3D"IntroforExponential4.x/3.xdevelopers-Existingconc=
eptsFAQ">Existing concepts FAQ</h1>
<h2 class=3D"western" id=3D"IntroforExponential4.x/3.xdevelopers-Settings">Se=
ttings</h2>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-inf=
ormation">
<span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-info confluence-informa=
tion-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
See=20
<a href=3D"https://doc.ez.no/display/EZP/Configuration" rel=3D"nofollow">ht=
tps://doc.ez.no/display/EZP/Configuration</a>
</div>
</div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<ul>
<li><p><strong>New-style settings:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><p>In a single yml file: <strong>exponential.yml</strong> for Exponential,=
 <strong>config.yml</strong> for other bundles (it is possible to <a href=
=3D"http://symfony.com/doc/current/book/page_creation.html#application-conf=
iguration" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">import other files from=
 here</a> as well).<br>Note that it's possible to specialize settings for s=
pecific environments (e.g. <code>exponential_dev.yml</code>, <code>config_dev=
.yml</code>)&nbsp;</p></li>
<li><p>3 scopes (<strong>global</strong> =3D=3D <strong>override</strong>; =
extension scope is gone)</p></li>
<li><p>Order of precedence between extensions (bundles) is set by bundle lo=
ading order.</p></li>
<li><p>Runtime siteaccess configuration is resolved through the <a href=3D"=
/display/EZP/Configuration">ConfigResolver service</a>.</p></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><strong>Some notes about generic (non-eZ) settings for Symfony</strong>=
<br>
<ul>
<li>Symfony supports 3 formats for config files: <strong>yml</strong>, <str=
ong>xml</strong>, <strong>php&nbsp;</strong>(eZ recommends <strong>yml</str=
ong>)</li>
<li>A single configuration file exists: <strong>config.yml</strong> (at lea=
st, in the final, compiled version, many files exist on disk)</li>
<li>A configuration file can include another one via the imports statement =
(e.g. <code>config_dev.yml</code> would import <code>config.yml</code>)</li=
>
<li>When creating a bundle, it is not sufficient to add a config file to it=
, the developer needs to specify that it is to be loaded (either via an imp=
ort statement from app/config/config.yml or via a ServiceContainer extensio=
n in php). <br>Note that if you use the <a href=3D"http://symfony.com/doc/c=
urrent/bundles/SensioGeneratorBundle/commands/generate_bundle.html" class=
=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">generator bundle command</a>, all neede=
d code will be automatically generated for you.</li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<h2 class=3D"western" id=3D"IntroforExponential4.x/3.xdevelopers-Siteaccesses=
">Siteaccesses</h2>
<ul>
<li><p>See <a href=3D"http://confluence.ez.no/display/EZP/Siteaccess+Matchi=
ng" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">http://confluence.ez.no/displa=
y/EZP/Siteaccess+Matching</a></p></li>
<li><p>Mostly unchanged</p></li>
<li><p>Better way of not duplicating settings: "groups" of siteaccesses</p>=
</li>
<li>Siteaccess settings <em>specializes</em> siteaccess group settings.</li=
>
<li><p>New way to define siteaccess: via environment variable (super-fast)<=
/p></li>
</ul>
<p style=3D"margin-left: 60.0px;"><strong>Q:</strong> Apart from host url a=
nd port, are any other matchers available (host+url, =E2=80=A6)</p>
<p style=3D"margin-left: 60.0px;"><strong>A:</strong> working on an improve=
d fleximatcher witch will be part of 5.1, this includes host+uri combined m=
atching</p>
<ul>
<li>Possible now to define custom siteaccess matchers.</li>
</ul>
<h2 class=3D"western" id=3D"IntroforExponential4.x/3.xdevelopers-Urls">Urls</=
h2>
<ul>
<li><p>More flexible routing system.</p></li>
<li><p>View parameters are still present.</p></li>
<li><p>Configuration done in yml file.</p></li>
<li><p>Making params optional is done by giving them a default value in the=
 config file</p></li>
</ul>
<p style=3D"margin-left: 30.0px;"><strong>Q:</strong> How is the siteaccess=
 part of urls managed (standard Sf code has no concept for this)?</p>
<p style=3D"margin-left: 30.0px;"><strong>A:</strong> The eZP stack uses an=
 enhanced router. This is transparent to developers.</p>
<p style=3D"margin-left: 30.0px;"><strong>Q:</strong>&nbsp;Support for link=
ing across siteaccess?</p>
<p style=3D"margin-left: 30.0px;"><strong>A:</strong>&nbsp;Yes, <a href=3D"=
/display/EZP/Language+Switcher">Language switcher</a></p>
<h2 class=3D"western" id=3D"IntroforExponential4.x/3.xdevelopers-Designs">Des=
igns</h2>
<p><strong>Q:</strong>&nbsp;How is the concept of designs + fallback suppor=
ted ?</p>
<p><strong>A:</strong>&nbsp;Planned for 5.future. Might reuse an Sf bundle =
from <a href=3D"https://github.com/liip/LiipThemeBundle" class=3D"external-=
link" rel=3D"nofollow">Liip which allows <em>themes</em></a> (theme =3D=3D =
design).</p>
<ul>
<li><p><strong>Side question:</strong> Can a tpl in one bundle override a t=
pl from another one?</p></li>
<li><p><strong>A:</strong> Yes, but via bundle inheritance a bundle can hav=
e only 1 child =E2=80=93 clearly not powerful enough compared to eZP4, but =
there seems to be progress in Symfony about improving this.</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 class=3D"western" id=3D"IntroforExponential4.x/3.xdevelopers-Templates(Tw=
ig)">Templates (Twig)</h2>
<p>Twig is a templating engine, used in the templates. Exponential Platform =
provides <a href=3D"https://doc.ez.no/display/EZP/Twig+Helper" rel=3D"nofol=
low">Twig helpers</a> and <a href=3D"https://doc.ez.no/display/EZP/Twig+fun=
ctions" rel=3D"nofollow">Twig functions</a>. You can also add your own Twig=
 helpers and functions.</p>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-inf=
ormation">
<span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-info confluence-informa=
tion-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<p>See <a href=3D"http://twig.sensiolabs.org/documentation" class=3D"extern=
al-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Twig documentation</a> and <a href=3D"http://symf=
ony.com/doc/current/book/templating.html" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"no=
follow">templating basics in Symfony</a>.</p>
</div>
</div>
<ul>
<li><p>For extending Twig, refer to&nbsp;<a href=3D"http://twig.sensiolabs.=
org/doc/advanced.html" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Twig develo=
per documentation</a> and <a href=3D"http://symfony.com/doc/current/cookboo=
k/templating/twig_extension.html" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">=
Symfony cookbook</a>.</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 class=3D"western" id=3D"IntroforExponential4.x/3.xdevelopers-i18n">i18n</=
h2>
<p>Refer to the <a href=3D"http://symfony.com/doc/current/book/translation.=
html" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">translation section in Symfo=
ny documentation</a>.</p>
<h2 class=3D"western" id=3D"IntroforExponential4.x/3.xdevelopers-LoadingCSSan=
djs">Loading CSS and js</h2>
<p>Best practice is to <a href=3D"http://symfony.com/doc/current/cookbook/a=
ssetic/index.html" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">use <strong>Ass=
etic</strong></a>.</p>
<h2 class=3D"western" id=3D"IntroforExponential4.x/3.xdevelopers-Caching">Cac=
hing</h2>
<p>Content cache is fully <a href=3D"http://symfony.com/doc/current/book/ht=
tp_cache.html" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Http cache</a>.</p>
<p style=3D"margin-left: 30.0px;"><strong>Q:</strong> How to clear caches f=
or Exponential 5? Is there a single action to clear caches for both stacks?<=
/p>
<p style=3D"margin-left: 30.0px;"><strong>A:</strong> Content (Http) cache =
is purged at publish time or from admin interface. You can use the <code>ca=
che:clear</code> command to clear all Symfony cache and in 'dev' environmen=
t is disabled (see <a href=3D"http://symfony.com/doc/2.0/cookbook/configura=
tion/environments.html" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Symfony do=
c on environments</a>) . No unified command yet.</p>
<h2 class=3D"western" id=3D"IntroforExponential4.x/3.xdevelopers-Using4-in-5"=
>Using 4-in-5</h2>
<p style=3D"margin-left: 30.0px;"><strong>Q:</strong> Will it always be pos=
sible to run the Legacy Stack as a standalone app?<span>&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style=3D"margin-left: 30.0px;"><span><strong>A:</strong> Yes.</span></p>
<p style=3D"margin-left: 30.0px;"><strong>Q:</strong> Is there any rewrite =
rule needed to access var/storage/images of old stack from within the vhost=
 of the new stack?</p>
<p style=3D"margin-left: 30.0px;"><strong>A:</strong> No, this is achieved =
by <em>symlinking</em>&nbsp;to <code>web/</code> the <code>design/</code>, =
<code>extension/</code>, <code>share/</code> and <code>var/</code> director=
ies of the Exponential legacy stack (done via <code>exponential:legacy:assets_=
install</code> script).</p>
<p style=3D"margin-left: 30.0px;">The official name for the Exponential 4.x =
stack included within Exponential 5.x is not Exponential 4.x but Exponential L=
egacy (+"Stack" in case of Exponential+extensions).<br><br></p>
<h2 class=3D"western" id=3D"IntroforExponential4.x/3.xdevelopers-Extensions">=
Extensions</h2>
<p style=3D"margin-left: 30.0px;"><strong>Q:</strong> Implemented as bundle=
s?</p>
<p style=3D"margin-left: 30.0px;"><strong>A:</strong> Yes.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p style=3D"margin-left: 30.0px;"><strong>Q:</strong> Declared as services =
with a special tag or naming convention? (see e.g. How twig registers stuff=
).</p>
<p style=3D"margin-left: 30.0px;"><strong>A:</strong>&nbsp;Reuse as much as=
 possible from Sf, do not enforce standards unless needed.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p style=3D"margin-left: 30.0px;"><strong>Q:</strong> Will need naming conv=
ention?</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p style=3D"margin-left: 30.0px;"><strong>Q:</strong> Installed via compose=
r?</p>
<p style=3D"margin-left: 30.0px;"><strong>A:</strong> Yes.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p style=3D"margin-left: 30.0px;"><span><strong>Q:</strong> What part of a =
website to put in <code>exponential/</code>, what part to put in <code>src/</=
code>? (equivalent of eZ =E2=80=9Call in extension=E2=80=9D dev </span><spa=
n>philosophy</span><span>)</span></p>
<p style=3D"margin-left: 30.0px;"><strong>A:</strong> <code>exponential/</cod=
e> is for global configuration/templates, <code>src/</code> is for site-spe=
cific developments.</p>
<ul>
<li style=3D"list-style-type: none;background-image: none;">
<ul>
<li><code>exponential_legacy/</code> is at root level because it is considere=
d as an application in itself.</li>
<li><p class=3D"_mce_tagged_br">All current extensions will be renamed with=
 LS suffix (for Legacy Stack) to distinguish them from new implementations.=
</p></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<p class=3D"_mce_tagged_br" style=3D"margin-left: 30.0px;"><strong>Q:</stro=
ng> Best practices for naming php classes (filenames and directories)?</p>
<p class=3D"_mce_tagged_br" style=3D"margin-left: 30.0px;"><strong>A:</stro=
ng> Follow <a href=3D"https://github.com/php-fig/fig-standards/blob/master/=
accepted/PSR-0.md" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">PSR-0</a>, with=
 namespaces. <br>&nbsp; &nbsp; See&nbsp;<a href=3D"http://symfony.com/doc/2=
.0/cookbook/bundles/best_practices.html" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nof=
ollow">http://symfony.com/doc/2.0/cookbook/bundles/best_practices.html</a><=
/p>
<h2 class=3D"western" id=3D"IntroforExponential4.x/3.xdevelopers-Debugging">D=
ebugging</h2>
